  "texts": [
    "We use the model sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L12-v2, which is a BERT model that produces a sequence of real-valued vectors of length 384.",
    "During pre-training on sentence similarity tasks, mean pooling is applied to encode each the sequence into a single vector.",
    "For details, we refer to Reimers & Gurevych (2019).",
    "We apply the approach directly to the test set, because no task-specific training is required.",
    "The resulting confusion matrix is shown in the left part of Figure 20, and the scores are shown in Table 9."
  ],
